The paper deals with a problem related to set-cover, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of queries to obtain information about the sets and elements suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The application of the covert set-cover problem to network discovery further supports the relevance to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and also to social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the use of randomized algorithms and analysis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC).
